Narnumru, Pomegranate and Egg. A unique recipe from the Azerbaijani cuisine. Sauteed onions with butter, juicy pomegranate arils and eggs would make this incredible dish!
Follow➡️ @homerecipes101
Facebook➡️ homerecipes101
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INGREDIENTS:
2 Tbsp butter
1/2 Cup yellow onions, finely chopped
1 Cup pomegranate arils
2 Eggs
Freshly ground black pepper 
Sea salt to taste 

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. In a medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onions and saute until tender and soft, about 5 minutes. Stir frequently.
2. Add pomegranate arils and cook covered until it gets juicy and soft. About 6-8 minutes.
3. Make two wells in the pomegranate, exposing the skillet underneath. Crack the eggs in each spot and season with salt and pepper, lower heat and cook covered until the whites are set and the eggs are cooked to your liking. Serve immediately with bread.

Eating more will only get you to your body's healthy weight quicker.

Le Bec Fin 
呢間係french-inspired Japanese restaurant，所以可以見到廚師會運用時令日本食材融入法國嘅烹調技巧

首先介紹吓其中一個四道菜嘅午市套餐
-duck breast salad
-gratinated drench onion soup en cocotte
-Spanish red prawn pasta
-creme caramel 

🥗所選用嘅蔬菜比普通嘅餐廳種類較特別，亦都真係好新鮮

🧄湯亦都真係好impressive，真材實料，芝士鋪面，而且即刻覺，同之前喺法國飲過嘅不相伯仲👍🏻

🦐🍝亦都絕不欺場，需知道平時食一隻紅蝦平既都差不多接近$200港幣，但係一碟意粉已經用咗五隻，食之前咁晒啲蝦膏出嚟，黏口香糯，蝦味濃郁

最後嘅🍮則較為普通

This AmAzing sandwich got me speechless!

Let me know how it turns out if you make this!
...
Ingredients
3 slices of whole wheat sandwich bread
1 medium-sized onion cut into rings
2 tomatoes cut into rings
2 sunny side up eggs
thinly sliced ham (I used Zwan luncheon meat which is essentially a chicken ham)
lettuce leaves
Salt
Black pepper
Mayonnaise
Finely grated cheese

1. Toast your bread for a few minutes until lightly brown and crispy
2. Set up your work station or countertop with the toppings in the sequence you want them to go on to your sandwich.
Starting from my far right, I have mayonnaise, lettuce, sunny side up egg, ham, tomatoes and onions. This is my preferred method for sandwich stacking, but by all means do what makes you satisfied.
3. Spread a slice of toasted bread with mayonnaise on one side, then layer with lettuce, a sunny side up egg, some slices of ham, some slices of tomatoes and finally some slices of onions in that order.
4. Season with salt and black pepper
5. Top this bottom stack with another slice of toasted bread already spread with a generous amount of mayonnaise, then repeat your stacking.
6. Season with salt and pepper
7. Top the two stacks with the final slice of toasted bread, also spread with a generous amount of mayonnaise. 
8. Now it's time for the taste test! Yum Yum
-

Pineapple Pepper Medley🍍

I like this side dish because it surprisingly pairs well with many diffferent entrées. 

Toss the peppers in about 2 T of pineapple juice, this will help the peppers caramelize a little. 

I fry the pineapple in 1:1 butter and olive oil. Then I use the same pan with a little more olive oil and sauté the peppers on high heat.

Then I add the chopped pineapple back to the pan just to warm them up.

Salt & Pepper then serve. 

This medley can also show up on taco or fajita night!

INGREDIENTS (Servings 6):
• ½ cup cherry tomatoes halved, or 3 vine-ropes tomatoes.
• 3 Persian cucumbers sliced.
• ½ small red onion sliced.
• ½ green pepper sliced.
• 4 ounces black kalamata olives.
• 8 ounces feta block.

GREEK SALAD DRESSING
• 4 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil.
• 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar.
• ½ teaspoon dried oregano.
• ¼ teaspoon salt.
• ¼ teaspoon black pepper.
.
INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Place the tomatoes, cucumbers, red onions, green peppers, olives and feta cheese in a large serving bowl.
2. Mix the ingredients of the salad dressing together in a small bowl and drizzle over the salad ingredients. Lightly toss to combine, being careful not to over-mix or break up the feta cheese (alternatively, toss everything and then add the feta blocks on top).
.
NUTRITION FACTS (For One Servings):
o Calories ~ 237kcal.
o Fat ~ 21g.
o Carbs ~ 8g.
o Fiber ~ 2g.
o Sugar ~ 5g.
o Protein ~ 7g.

The big talk in the restaurant industry right now is a $15 minimum wage. There’s a lot of worry about it not being viable because profit margins are already so slim for a restaurant. But since we are going to raise prices anyway due to insane food cost inflation we figure why not also include a $15 minimum wage for our employees in that price hike? So, starting in March the price of our lunch sandwiches will go up, breakfast and salads will remain the same price, and our employees will be making a $15 minimum wage. So one way or another I guess we will see if it is viable ( I feel like it is) and hopefully put naysayers to rest. Everyone deserves a livable wage.
